The paper deals with path planning for multiple UAVs and a ground vehicle, which is a common problem in robotics and automation. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, such as Mixed Integer Quadratic Programming (MIQP) and Random Key Genetic Algorithm (RKGA), which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.MA). The paper also deals with system-level optimization, which falls under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves optimization of large-scale problems, which is a common theme in Large Scale Data Management (cs.LG).
